<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-F9E89CD5-31DA-4B47-B08E-B837C38B21C2" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-F9E89CD5-31DA-4B47-B08E-B837C38B21C2" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">19 Print without winding</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-D40CABC6-5397-4576-85C3-E1F1C3386B34"><p class="- topic/p ">You can also print without winding. Media that is printed without winding can be transported well and is not too weak. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-1CD904A8-212A-4CE2-8F8D-30BEFEE0B837" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ul id="UL_B5A4DF99AE1444DAADEEEFA23632434A" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_D7997D9B55584B17BADCECF9E05CCEC4" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Check the media category of your media. Media categories that need a tension bar cannot be printed without winding. 
</p></li><li id="LI_4D1FBBA8C9EE4F15B1DA63BFC6C1280B" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Printing without winding is set in the media type configuration in the RIP software. For printing without winding you must select <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">no tension bar</uicontrol></ph> under <ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Winding tension</uicontrol></ph>.
</p></li><li id="LI_79DD8A093D5849B68E2619B4F77C683F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The printer is ready to print. 
</p></li></ul></prereq><steps id="GUID-021FF504-6A07-4992-BC15-F6DDFB0F3481" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step id="STEP_6DC11A1C61FA40B1BE34D52CC7EE3CF3" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the operator panel tap on the <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Output</text></uicontrol></ph> icon. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_2BF18C6C01B44B1C810A0B5D06861661" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Make sure <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Wind the output</text></uicontrol></ph> is set to <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">No</text></uicontrol></ph>. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_11EA92FE3A7142C39B96BE8F38CA9AEC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0A9A883C-81D6-4AA0-8F74-5CFD2BA87DCA-low.png" id="IMAGE_15EBD5DD621F42CEB6676B847EA82EAD" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0A9A883C-81D6-4AA0-8F74-5CFD2BA87DCA-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_CD132A4E8144424AB15786C3D7BCA08A" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Start a print job. The printer continues printing without winding. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_180BA725A4AD4FB9968F0373EADC7BC7" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0E7B9128-33B5-4B8F-A470-ABC07FC543D6-low.png" id="IMAGE_71800526351C4A58A570C62EEBE0537D" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0E7B9128-33B5-4B8F-A470-ABC07FC543D6-low.png"/></fig></info></step></steps><postreq id="GUID-91479708-15B5-42A2-AD33-B1A0914EA508" class="- topic/section task/postreq "><p class="- topic/p ">When you want to stop printing without winding you have to cut the media. 
</p></postreq></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-77E3E148-DF16-4838-9432-CE905B393B0C.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
